# Language Policy

## Code Comments
- Write ALL code comments in **English only**
- No Chinese comments, no mixed language comments
- Comments should explain the "why", not the "what"

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Chinese comment
// 计算用户分数
const score = calculateScore();

// ✅ GOOD - English comment
// Calculate user score based on quiz responses
const score = calculateScore();
```

## User Communication
- Respond in **English** by default
- Only switch to other languages (e.g., Chinese) when the user explicitly requests it
- If user writes in Chinese, respond in Chinese
- If user writes in English, respond in English

## File Naming
- Use English file names only (no Chinese characters)

## Documentation
- README files, docs, and inline documentation must be in English

## Variable/Function Names
- Always use English identifiers
- No pinyin or Chinese characters in code
